=begin

Write a regex that matches `'blueberry'` or `'blackberry'`, where
`'berry'` can be written in the pattern only once.

Test cases:
  'blueberry'
  'blackberry'
  'black berry'
  'strawberry'

=end

berries = ['blueberry', 'blackberry', 'black berry', 'strawberry']

berries.each do |berry|
  puts berry.match(/(blue|black)berry/)
end
